items.text: DOCTORS Without Borders (MSF) suspends operations at NASSER HOSPITAL in GAZA after armed personnel block medical access — latest escalation in humanitarian crisis following ISRAEL military restrictions (Al Jazeera)

U.S. exploring potential new military base in THAILAND - strategic shift in INDO-PACIFIC positioning amid CHINA tensions. Ongoing diplomatic negotiations with BANGKOK government. No final agreement confirmed (The Diplomat)

INDONESIA commits up to 8,000 troops as first major Muslim-majority nation to potential GAZA peacekeeping force - direct challenge to ISRAEL's military operations, significant diplomatic escalation (UN Security Council)

U.S. NAVY deploys multiple CARRIER STRIKE GROUPS near SOUTH CHINA SEA - F-35 fighters accompany USS RONALD REAGAN, USS NIMITZ battle groups in direct challenge to CHINA territorial claims (19FortyFive)

GLOBAL NUCLEAR TENSIONS escalate: Major arms control organizations signal urgent diplomatic efforts to prevent potential new nuclear arms race between US, RUSSIA, CHINA — strategic negotiations at critical juncture (Arms Control Association)
U.S. MILITARY adapting SPY SATELLITE capabilities amid growing SPACE WEAPONS threat — shifting from pure reconnaissance to active defense/countermeasure roles (Defense One)

INDIA-linked suspect NIKHIL GUPTA charged in assassination plot against US-based SIKH separatist GURPATWANT SINGH PANNUN — potential state-sponsored murder attempt against diaspora activist. Faces up to 40 years if convicted (BBC)
UKRAINE strikes BK-16 landing craft in CRIMEA - confirmed naval attack damages RUSSIAN maritime capabilities in Black Sea region (Kyiv Independent)
DOCTORS WITHOUT BORDERS halts medical operations at GAZA hospital - cites armed personnel presence, compromising humanitarian mission (Times of Israel)

NEW START nuclear arms control treaty between RUSSIA and USA officially expires - first time since 1991 no active strategic nuclear weapons limitation agreement in place (Sunday Guardian)

NORTH KOREA launches multiple BALLISTIC MISSILES into SEA OF JAPAN - third missile test in 72 hours, provocative action amid regional tensions (Reuters)
THAILAND conducts airstrikes along CAMBODIA border — active military engagement reported in disputed territorial region. Potential escalation of long-standing border tensions (Reuters)

LIBYA: Ongoing human trafficking crisis documented - migrants systematically sold into slavery, primarily from SUB-SAHARAN AFRICA, with estimated 50,000+ individuals trafficked since 2015 (Frontiers Research)
SUDAN conflict: ETHIOPIA and UAE facing international pressure over alleged support for opposing factions in ongoing civil war - potential external intervention complicating regional stability (DW)
